Vulnerability.Description: A maliciously crafted command line for kdesu can result in the user only seeing part of the commands that will actually get executed as super user.
Vulnerability.Name: CVE-2016-7787

Vulnerability.Description: The WLS Security component in Oracle WebLogic Server 10.3.6.0, 12.1.2.0, 12.1.3.0, and 12.2.1.0 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object in T3 protocol traffic to TCP port 7001, related to oracle_common/modules/com.bea.core.apache.commons.collections.jar. NOTE: the scope of this CVE is limited to the WebLogic Server product.
Vulnerability.Name: CVE-2015-4852
